h2. Bean 'processEngine'

You can use the *[org.camunda.bpm.engine.ProcessEngine|http://docs.camunda.org/latest/api-references/javadoc/org/camunda/bpm/engine/ProcessEngine.html]* 
as an injectable bean:

{code}
def processEngine
{code}

The plugin registers the bean as 'camundaProcessEngineBean' with the default alias 'processEngine'.
You can change this default alias via [configuration|guide:bean-names].